Sat May 30 05:33:23 UTC 2026 - Martin Pluskal <mpluskal@suse.com>

- Update to version 2.0+git.20260514:
  * Add PSP Security Protocol support: script-parser
    encapsulation, header parsing, psp_state and
    psp_rx_assoc/psp_tx_assoc syscalls, real AES-GCM crypto,
    ynl-c based libraries, and BPF-filter/iptables handling
    plus test cases
  * Add Accurate ECN (AccECN) TCP option support and expose
    AccECN counters/status and ecn_mode through tcpi
  * Sync struct _tcp_info with the v6.16 kernel uAPI header
  * Print TCP option names and contents instead of the
    numerical kind
  * Assorted test-harness and README improvements
- Rebase make-build-more-consistent-with-openSUSE-packaging.patch
  for the restructured upstream Makefiles; the -static removal it
  used to carry is now the upstream default, so only the
  CFLAGS/LDFLAGS handling remains
- Build with -fno-strict-aliasing and drop the spec's own -Werror
  and -Wno-* flags: the checksum code type-puns the packet buffer,
  which -O2 strict aliasing miscompiled and made checksum_test fail;
  the distribution build flags are now used as-is (only
  -fno-strict-aliasing is added)

